16:38.200 --> 16:39.019
- WHAT?
- THE CORNER.

16:39.130 --> 16:40.506
- YOU DID?

16:40.620 --> 16:41.644
- AND WAITED IN MY CAR UNTIL
IT SEEMED APPROPRIATE--

16:41.750 --> 16:42.614
- YOU WAITED IN THE CAR?

16:42.720 --> 16:43.402
- YEAH.
- OH, NO.

16:43.510 --> 16:44.716
- WELL, I HAVE...
- WHAT DID YOU DO?

16:44.830 --> 16:45.512
- I HAVE--I HAVE THINGS TO DO.

16:45.620 --> 16:46.689
I WAS LISTENING TO THE RADIO
AND,

16:46.790 --> 16:48.348
- WHAT DID YOU DO?

16:48.450 --> 16:50.338
- YOU KNOW, CAUGHT UP ON CURRENT
EVENTS AND THINGS LIKE THAT.

16:50.450 --> 16:52.315
[laughter]

16:52.420 --> 16:54.149
- I WAS ALWAYS THINK IT RUNS IN
THE FAMILY

16:54.250 --> 16:55.478
SO IT'S NOT MY FAULT,
YOU KNOW.

16:55.600 --> 16:56.385
- TARDINESS?

16:56.490 --> 16:57.969
- ME AND CROSBY,
WE STRUGGLE.

16:58.080 --> 16:59.524
- NOT SO MUCH.
- IT'S NOT OUR FAULT.

16:59.630 --> 17:00.528
- IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

17:00.640 --> 17:02.562
MY BROTHER'S ALWAYS--

17:02.670 --> 17:04.729
