20:24.320 --> 20:27.949
FEEL FOR THE FROWNING NOW

20:28.050 --> 20:35.468
NOWHERE TO BEGIN,
ARE YOU TO FIGURE IT OUT?

20:35.570 --> 20:38.198
WOULDN'T YOU LIKE TO KNOW?

20:38.300 --> 20:40.097
WOULDN'T YOU LIKE
TO KNOW

20:40.200 --> 20:43.749
WOULDN'T YOU LIKE TO KNOW

20:43.860 --> 20:48.138
- UM, SHOULD I--SHOULD I PARK
THIS SOMEWHERE DOWN THE STREET?

20:48.240 --> 20:52.552
- I WOULD LOVE TO,
BUT I--I FORGOT.

20:52.660 --> 20:55.208
I WAS JUST THINKING OF IT
THAT I HAVE A DEADLINE

20:55.320 --> 20:56.651
FOR MY WRITING CLASS TOMORROW.

20:56.770 --> 20:58.931
- OKAY.
- SO, MAYBE NOT TONIGHT.

20:59.050 --> 21:00.278
- NO PROBLEM.
- I'M SORRY.

21:00.390 --> 21:01.732
- NO, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO APOLOGIZE.

21:01.840 --> 21:07.153
I KNOW THAT THE TIMING WASN'T
RIGHT TWO YEARS AGO,

21:07.260 --> 21:12.288
BUT IT SEEMS LIKE THE TIMING IS
RIGHT NOW FOR ME AT LEAST.

21:12.400 --> 21:18.373
AND I JUST--I GUESS I WANTED TO
LET YOU KNOW THAT

21:18.480 --> 21:23.440
THIS SIDE OF THE CAR
IS READY NOW,

21:23.550 --> 21:27.065
AND I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT THAT SIDE OF THE CAR.

21:27.180 --> 21:28.408
ABOUT IT OR ANYTHING.

21:28.520 --> 21:33.457
I JUST WANTED
YOU KNOW THAT I'M IN.

21:41.920 --> 21:45.435
- I DON'T KNOW.

21:48.990 --> 21:52.027
I DON'T KNOW WHY,
BUT I JUST DON'T KNOW.

21:56.970 --> 21:58.096
I'LL TALK TO YOU TOMORROW.

21:58.210 --> 21:59.370
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

21:59.490 --> 22:00.377
THANK YOU AGAIN.

22:00.490 --> 22:01.934
- YEAH.
- YEAH.

22:04.900 --> 22:06.788
[starts engine]

22:08.110 --> 22:10.419
WOULDN'T YOU LIKE TO KNOW

22:10.530 --> 22:14.569
THE ODDS OF BEING ALONE

22:19.060 --> 22:21.699
[school bell ringing]

22:21.820 --> 22:23.959
- ZACK, HI.

22:24.060 --> 22:26.096
- HEY.

22:26.200 --> 22:28.373
- UM...

22:28.480 --> 22:33.793
I'M SO SORRY.
I'M--I'M SO SORRY.

22:33.900 --> 22:35.583
I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT
THAT HAPPENED.

22:35.690 --> 22:37.897
IT WAS A COMPLETE
MISUNDERSTANDING.

22:39.970 --> 22:41.972
HE FEELS TERRIBLE.

22:42.080 --> 22:44.139
- OKAY.

22:44.250 --> 22:48.846
- I CAN UNDERSTAND THAT YOU'RE
MAD, AND YOU CAN BE MAD.

22:48.950 --> 22:52.010
I JUST FEEL LIKE THERE'S
PROBABLY ANOTHER WAY

22:52.120 --> 22:54.816
THAT WE COULD WORK THIS OUT
OTHER THAN LIKE PRESSING CHARGES

22:54.920 --> 22:57.263
JUST BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,
HE COULD GO TO JAIL.

22:57.370 --> 23:00.476
IT DOESN'T FEEL LIKE IT WAS THAT
BAD OF A THING AND I'M SORRY.

23:00.580 --> 23:01.956
- LOOK, IF IT WAS UP TO ME,

23:02.070 --> 23:04.129
I WOULD DROP THE CHARGES
IN A SECOND, OKAY?

23:04.240 --> 23:05.969
BUT MY PARENTS ARE
REALLY PISSED.

23:06.070 --> 23:09.892
- DID YOU EXPLAIN, LIKE,
THE CIRCUMSTANCES?

23:10.000 --> 23:11.001
- YEAH, YEAH.

23:11.110 --> 23:13.761
DUDE HAS A RECORD.

23:13.870 --> 23:16.930
- HE DOESN'T HAVE A RECORD.

23:17.050 --> 23:18.494
- YEAH, HE DOES ACTUALLY.

23:18.600 --> 23:21.046
ATTEMPTED MURDER AND ROBBERY.

23:21.150 --> 23:21.946
- SORRY.

23:22.050 --> 23:23.665
I KNOW ALEX,
AND HE WOULDN'T DO THAT.

23:23.780 --> 23:25.259
AND HE DOESN'T HAVE A RECORD.

23:25.360 --> 23:33.859
- WELL, MAYBE HE WOULDN'T,
BUT HE DID.

23:33.960 --> 23:46.384
[school bell rings]
[indistinct chatter]

23:46.490 --> 23:50.699
- HI.
I'M MAX BRAVERMAN.

23:55.640 --> 23:57.494
- I LOOKED YOU IN THE EYE.

23:57.600 --> 23:59.739
- WHAT HIS PROBLEM?

24:11.790 --> 24:15.089
- WHAT ARE YOU READING?

24:15.210 --> 24:20.557
- YEAH.

24:22.630 --> 24:25.929
- YOU PROBABLY HEARD I HAD
A VISITOR THE OTHER NIGHT.

24:26.050 --> 24:30.328
- YEP.
I HEARD.

24:30.430 --> 24:31.829
- I LIKE HIM.

24:31.950 --> 24:33.599
- THAT'S NICE.

24:33.710 --> 24:37.294
- AND HE'S 28.

24:37.400 --> 24:39.265
- YEAH, 28 IS KIND OF YOUNG.

24:39.370 --> 24:41.474
- HE WAS TWO YEARS OLD WHEN
THE BREAKFAST CLUBCAME OUT.

24:41.580 --> 24:43.889
- WOW, WAS THAT LONG AGO?
- YEAH, YEAH.

24:43.990 --> 24:45.617
AND WE'RE IN THE CAR
THE OTHER NIGHT,

24:45.720 --> 24:47.517
AND I KNOW MUSIC,
I'M NOT, YOU KNOW,

24:47.620 --> 24:49.895
BUT HE'S PLAYING THIS STUFF
CALLED NAKED KIDS.

24:50.000 --> 24:51.752
I'VE NEVER EVEN HEARD
ABOUT THEM.

24:51.860 --> 24:53.248
- YOU'VE NEVER HEARD
OF NAKED KIDS?

24:53.350 --> 24:54.487
- YOU HAVE?

24:54.590 --> 24:57.343
- LOOK, THESE ARE NOT
LEGITIMATE CONCERNS

24:57.460 --> 24:59.178
OF MOVIES AND MUSIC GROUPS.

24:59.290 --> 25:01.429
WHAT'S THE REAL DEAL?

25:01.530 --> 25:04.419
- I MEAN, I SHOULD BE
WITH SOMEONE MY OWN AGE,

25:05.710 --> 25:07.211
- MAYBE.
NOT NECESSARILY.

25:07.330 --> 25:09.423
YOU KNOW, IF YOU WERE
WITH SOMEONE WHO WAS 40,

25:09.540 --> 25:13.670
HE COULD BE TWICE DIVORCED
AND HAVE FIVE KIDS, YOU KNOW.

25:13.780 --> 25:15.463
I MEAN, THERE--THERE COULD
ALWAYS BE AN ISSUE

25:15.580 --> 25:20.062
IF YOU WANTED TO MAKE AN ISSUE.

25:20.170 --> 25:21.990
RELAX.
HAVE A GOOD TIME.

25:22.100 --> 25:27.299
YOU KNOW, ENJOY YOURSELF,
YEAH?

25:27.420 --> 25:31.140
- WHO CAN DO THAT?

25:31.250 --> 25:34.139
- WHAT'S STOPPING YOU?

25:34.250 --> 25:40.701
WHAT'S STOPPING YOU?

25:40.810 --> 25:42.539
- HOW DID CROSBY CONVINCE
YOU TO GIVE HIM

25:42.640 --> 25:45.154
MY SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER?
- WHAT?

25:45.260 --> 25:47.535
- WHY DID YOU GIVE CROSBY
MY SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER?

25:47.640 --> 25:50.529
- OH.

25:50.650 --> 25:55.235
WELL, HE SAID HE NEEDED IT.

25:55.340 --> 25:56.477
- ALL RIGHT.
WELL, LISTEN.

25:56.580 --> 25:57.820
YOU KNOW WHAT HE DID WITH IT?

25:57.930 --> 25:59.340
HE PUT MY NAME DOWN
ON A LOAN APPLICATION

25:59.450 --> 26:00.849
WITH THAT INFORMATION.

26:00.970 --> 26:02.995
HE IMPLICATED ME AS PARTNER
IN HIS NEW BUSINESS.

26:03.110 --> 26:04.896
- NO.
- YEAH.

26:05.010 --> 26:05.965
- REALLY?

26:06.080 --> 26:07.104
- OKAY, SO I NEED
YOUR HELP HERE.

26:07.220 --> 26:08.380
I NEED YOU TO JUST REMIND ME
OF ALL THE WAYS

26:08.490 --> 26:09.354
THAT CROSBY IS A SCREW UP,
OKAY?

26:09.460 --> 26:10.552
- HE'S IMPULSIVE.

26:10.670 --> 26:13.070
I MEAN, MY GOSH, HE THINKS
EVERYBODY FEELS

26:13.190 --> 26:14.873
THE SAME WAY ABOUT STUFF
THAT HE DOES,

26:14.980 --> 26:17.562
AND IF HE FINDS OUT THAT YOU'RE
ON A DIFFERENT PAGE THAN HE IS,

26:17.670 --> 26:18.534
WHAT YOU...
- TOTALLY DIFFERENT PAGE.

26:18.640 --> 26:19.493
- HE GETS UPSET.
- YEAH.

26:19.610 --> 26:21.191
LIKE A LITTLE BABY.

26:21.300 --> 26:23.222
- THAT KID HAS MANAGE TO LOSE
EVERY TOOL I'VE EVER OWNED.

26:23.340 --> 26:24.261
- NOT SURPRISING.

26:24.370 --> 26:26.053
- HE GOES THROUGH WOMEN
LIKE COTTON CANDY.

26:26.170 --> 26:28.309
- DAD, DON'T FORGET HE SLEPT
WITH MY SON'S BEHAVIORAL AIDE.

26:28.410 --> 26:30.298
AND, YOU KNOW, EVERY TIME WE GO
OUT FOR A MEAL,

26:30.410 --> 26:31.616
GUESS WHO HAS TO PICK UP
THE CHECK.

26:31.720 --> 26:32.709
- YOU DO?
- I DO.

26:32.830 --> 26:33.990
- WHEN HE WAS 16,
HE STOLE MY CAR,

26:34.100 --> 26:35.237
HE BASHED IT INTO
A GARBAGE CAN.

26:35.350 --> 26:36.339
- REMEMBER THIS?

26:36.450 --> 26:37.371
- TEARS THE BUMPER OFF.

26:37.490 --> 26:38.411
GUESS WHO ENDS UP PAYING FOR IT?

26:38.520 --> 26:39.418
- YOU?
- YEAH, ME.

26:39.520 --> 26:40.930
- SURE.
- WHY?

26:41.040 --> 26:42.314
- HE'S NOT GONNA PAY FOR IT.
- YOU NEVER PAID FOR IT.

26:42.420 --> 26:43.409
- YOU KNOW WHAT? HE TAKES STUFF
WITHOUT ASKING.

26:43.530 --> 26:45.737
BORROWS MONEY,
DOESN'T PAY IT BACK.

26:45.840 --> 26:47.637
AND YOU KNOW WHAT
REALLY BOTHERS ME?

26:47.740 --> 26:49.184
THIS IS KIND OF CRAZY,
BUT SOMETIMES, YOU KNOW,

26:49.290 --> 26:51.429
HE WEARS THE SAME SHIRT
TWO DAYS IN A ROW.

26:51.540 --> 26:54.600
- YEAH.
WELL, I DO THAT.

26:54.710 --> 26:56.257
- YEAH.
WELL, YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW,

26:56.370 --> 26:58.224
I MEAN UNLESS YOUR CAMPING,
IT'S KINDA GROSS.

26:58.340 --> 27:00.399
- UM-HMM.
- ANYWAY...

27:00.510 --> 27:01.431
- BOY.
SON, I GOT TO TELL YOU,

27:01.550 --> 27:03.199
I UNDERSTAND PERFECT LY,

27:03.310 --> 27:06.234
COMPLETELY OF WHY YOU WOULDN'T
GO INTO BUSINESS WITH HIM.

27:06.340 --> 27:08.479
- YEAH, AND YET YOU GIVE HIM
MY SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER.

27:08.590 --> 27:12.481
- IT JUST SEEMED TO MEAN
SO MUCH TO HIM.

27:12.590 --> 27:16.458
WHEN HE TOLD ME,
I SWEAR TO GOD,

27:16.560 --> 27:20.621
HE HAD TEARS IN HIS EYES.

27:20.740 --> 27:23.208
- YOU SUCK, DAD.

27:23.330 --> 27:28.154
YOU SUCK.

27:28.260 --> 27:29.488
- NOW, YOU SAY HELLO
TO YOU MOTHER.

27:29.610 --> 27:31.328
- YEAH.

27:31.440 --> 27:32.293
- AND I'LL BE OUT HERE.

27:32.400 --> 27:34.641
- OH, YEAH.

27:34.750 --> 27:36.194
- I GOT STUCK
IN SOME TRAFFIC

27:36.300 --> 27:38.404
COMING FROM THE PRESS
CONFERENCE. UH-HUH.

27:38.510 --> 27:40.159
YEAH, I PROBABLY ABOUT
20 MINUTES.

27:40.270 --> 27:43.205
OKAY, THAN KS.

28:02.850 --> 28:05.364
- IT VERY CLEARLY STATES THAT
YOU HAVE THE APARTMENT

28:05.470 --> 28:08.644
THROUGH JANUARY 2012,
SO THIS WILL BE NO PROBLEM.

28:08.750 --> 28:11.127
- [sighs]
THAT'S HUGE.

28:11.240 --> 28:13.617
MY LIFE IS SUCH A TRAIN WRECK
RIGHT NOW.

28:13.720 --> 28:14.823
I WAS REALLY HOPING SLEEPING ON
THE STREETS

28:14.930 --> 28:17.990
WASN'T GONNA BE PART OF IT.
[sighs]

28:18.110 --> 28:21.273
- I'M SURE WHAT YOU'RE DOING
IS NOT EASY.

28:21.380 --> 28:23.075
- I'M NOT THE FIRST DUMBASS
TO GET KNOCKED UP

28:23.180 --> 28:26.627
WHEN SHE WASN'T SUPPOSED TO, SO
I CAN'T FEEL TOO BAD FOR MYSELF.

28:26.730 --> 28:28.732
I WAS RAISED CATHOLIC.
- UH-HMM.

28:28.840 --> 28:31.968
- I GUESS I'M NOT ANYMORE,
BUT, YOU KNOW,

28:32.080 --> 28:34.150
AT THE END OF THE DAY,
YOU STILL HEAR THE HYMNS.

28:34.260 --> 28:36.012
- NO, I KIND OF WISH
THAT I HAD A RELIGION.

28:36.120 --> 28:37.633
WE WEREN'T RAISED
WITH ANYTHING SPECIFIC.

28:37.750 --> 28:40.742
- THE AGENCY FORM I FILLED OUT
ASKED IF I HAD A PREFERENCE

28:40.850 --> 28:42.260
FOR THE ADOPTED PARENTS'
RELIGION...

28:42.370 --> 28:43.120
- UH-HMM.

28:43.230 --> 28:45.926
- AND I JUST
KEPT THINKING NONE.

28:46.030 --> 28:47.338
- YOU'RE WORKING WITH AN AGENCY?

28:47.440 --> 28:48.919
- YEAH.

28:49.030 --> 28:51.476
I GUESS THERE'S ALREADY SOME
HUGE WAITING LIST FOR BABIES.

28:51.590 --> 28:53.410
I GUESS SOME PEOPLE HAVE
TROUBLE GETTING PREGNANT.

28:53.520 --> 28:55.659
- YEAH.
YEAH.

28:55.760 --> 29:01.289
I GUESS SO.

29:02.360 --> 29:03.691
- ARE YOU OKAY?

29:03.810 --> 29:04.834
DO YOU NEED SOME WATER
OR SOMETHING?

29:04.950 --> 29:07.350
- NO.
I DON'T KNOW.

29:07.460 --> 29:10.156
I'M HUNGRY OR SOMETHING,
I THINK I'VE SKIPPED LUNCH.

29:10.260 --> 29:11.534
- I CAN GO STEAL YOU SOME
FROM THE CART.

29:11.640 --> 29:12.629
- NO, NO, NO.

29:12.750 --> 29:13.944
- NO ONE'S GONNA NOTICE.
IT'S OKAY, TRUST ME.

29:14.060 --> 29:15.914
- I--LET ME JUST TAKE ONE MORE
LOOK AT YOUR LEASE,

29:16.030 --> 29:19.158
AND THEN I'LL GIVE IT BACK TO
YOU, AND WE'LL BE GOOD.

29:27.800 --> 29:29.131
[knocks on desk]

29:29.250 --> 29:30.239
- HEY, KRISTINA.

29:30.350 --> 29:31.829
- HI, MS. MCKENDO.

29:31.940 --> 29:33.908
HOW ARE YOU DOING?
- I'M GOOD.

29:34.010 --> 29:36.149
- I JUST--I WANTED TO SEE
IF I COULD TALK TO YOU

29:36.250 --> 29:37.808
FOR A COUPLE OF MINUTES.
I BROUGHT A COFFEE...

29:37.910 --> 29:38.877
- NO, I GOTTA GO.

29:38.980 --> 29:40.117
- THOUGHT WE COULD SPEAK
FOR A SECOND.

29:40.220 --> 29:41.255
I SENT YOU A COUPLE OF EMAILS.
- OH, NINE, I THINK.

29:41.360 --> 29:43.248
- REGARDING MAX--I KNOW
THAT'S A LOT FOR FOUR DAYS

29:43.360 --> 29:45.737
BUT I JUST REALLY WANTED TO TALK
WITH YOU ABOUT MAX'S PROGRESS.

29:45.850 --> 29:46.669
- RIGHT.
- I BROUGHT US A COFFEE.

29:46.780 --> 29:48.224
- NO, I KNOW.

29:48.330 --> 29:49.297
- I THOUGHT WE COULD SIT AND
TAKE A MOMENT JUST TO TALK.

29:49.400 --> 29:50.606
- LISTEN, I'M GONNA GET
TO THOSE.

29:50.710 --> 29:51.677
I'M GONNA GET TO
ALL MY EMAILS TONIGHT.

29:51.790 --> 29:52.677
I'LL GET TO IT, TONIGHT.

29:52.790 --> 29:56.544
- OKAY, GREAT.
YOU KNOW WHAT, PLEASE.

29:56.650 --> 29:59.130
PLEASE, I JUST--I REALLY WOULD
LIKE TO TALK TO YOU FOR JUST--

29:59.240 --> 30:01.276
IT'LL TAKE FIVE MINUTES.
THAT'S IT.

30:01.380 --> 30:02.301
- OKAY.
- OKAY?

30:02.420 --> 30:04.627
- ALL RIGHT.
SIT--SIT DOWN. LET'S...

30:04.730 --> 30:06.891
- IF I WEREN'T WORRIED,
I WOULDN'T--

30:07.010 --> 30:08.386
I WOULDN'T HAVE BARGED
IN LIKE THIS.

30:08.490 --> 30:12.870
BUT MAX'S DAD AND I TOOK
A HUGE--HUGE LEAP OF FAITH

30:12.980 --> 30:15.073
BY SENDING HIM TO THE SCHOOL
AND MAINSTREAMING HIM.

30:15.190 --> 30:15.940
- RIGHT.

30:16.050 --> 30:19.395
WELL, WHY DID YOU
MAINSTREAM HIM?

30:19.500 --> 30:21.252
- WELL, WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
DO YOU THINK IT WAS A BAD IDEA?

30:21.370 --> 30:22.849
BECAUSE I FOUGHT MY HUSBAND
ON IT FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

30:22.950 --> 30:25.601
- NO, NO, I DON'T--I'M NOT
SAYING IT WAS A BAD IDEA,

30:25.720 --> 30:28.188
I'M ASKING WHY YOU DID IT.

30:28.300 --> 30:29.927
- SO HE COULD BE
ACADEMICALLY CHALLENGED.

30:30.030 --> 30:32.681
- AND HE WILL BE.
HE'S EXTREMELY BRIGHT.

30:32.790 --> 30:36.681
- I JUST--I WORRY BECAUSE,
I'M GONNA SOUND LIKE A WEIRDO,

30:36.800 --> 30:39.030
BUT I ACTUALLY LEI-T WORK
YESTERDAY

30:39.140 --> 30:41.199
JUST TO SORT OF SPY ON HIM,

30:41.320 --> 30:42.526
JUST TO SEE HOW HE WAS DOING,

30:42.630 --> 30:45.485
AND COPING, AND I'M WORRIED
ABOUT HIM SOCIALLY

30:45.600 --> 30:49.286
AND I CAME TO SCHOOL, AND I SAW
HIM SITTING ON--ON THE TABLE

30:49.390 --> 30:52.666
BY HIMSELF AT LUNCH TIME.
AND I JUST GET A LITTLE CONCERN.

30:52.780 --> 30:54.156
I KNOW I SOUND
LIKE A TOTAL FREAK,

30:54.260 --> 30:57.741
AND I'M JUST--I'M VERY EMOTIONAL
BECAUSE OF HORMONES AND...

30:57.850 --> 30:59.329
- YOU'RE NOT FREAK.

30:59.440 --> 31:02.785
IT'S--YOU'RE JUST GONNA HAVE
TO GET A LITTLE MORE COMFORTABLE

31:02.890 --> 31:07.782
WITH HAVING LESS CONTROL.

31:07.900 --> 31:09.208
- THAT'S GONNA BE REALLY
HARD FOR ME.

31:09.310 --> 31:10.231
- I KNOW.

31:10.350 --> 31:11.658
- COULD I MAYBE GET
YOUR HOME NUMBER?

31:11.760 --> 31:13.682
[laughs]
I'M JUST KIDDING.

31:13.800 --> 31:16.792
I WOULDN'T DO THAT TO YOU.
I MEAN.

31:16.900 --> 31:20.176
- I'LL TRY TO BE
A LITTLE MORE...

31:20.290 --> 31:21.279
- THANKS.

31:21.390 --> 31:22.357
- ANSWER THE EMAILS
A LITTLE QUICKER.

31:22.460 --> 31:24.212
- OKAY.

31:24.330 --> 31:25.877
- HE'LL BE FINE!

31:30.880 --> 31:32.461
[knocks on door]

31:32.580 --> 31:33.467
- AHEM.
- HEY.

31:33.580 --> 31:34.433
- HEY.

31:34.540 --> 31:37.816
UM, SO, I GAVE MY LANDLORD
THAT LETTER,

31:37.930 --> 31:40.398
AND HE COMPLETELY BACKED OFF.

31:40.510 --> 31:42.751
LIKE, I'D NEVER SEEN HIM
SO TERRIFIED.

31:42.860 --> 31:44.134
- [laughs]

31:44.240 --> 31:47.277
- SO--UM, I GOT YOU
A FREE COFFEE.

31:47.380 --> 31:49.007
IT'S NOT QUITE
FREE LEGAL ADVICE,

31:49.110 --> 31:51.032
BUT IT'S GOOD
WITH A DOUGHNUT.

31:51.150 --> 31:54.313
- [laughs]
WELL, I'M GLAD I COULD HELP,

31:54.420 --> 31:59.972
AND THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR THE COFFEE.

32:00.090 --> 32:05.778
- IF--IF THERE'S EVER ANYTHING
I CAN DO FOR--FOR YOU,

32:05.880 --> 32:10.499
I MEAN, I KNOW SOME PRETTY COOL
CAPOEIRA MOVES, YOU KNOW.

32:10.610 --> 32:12.953
- THAT MAYBE COULD COME
IN HANDY, THANKS.

32:13.060 --> 32:14.129
- TAEIQNONDO?

32:14.240 --> 32:20.065
- I GUESS, I'M JUST--
THANK YOU.

32:24.010 --> 32:29.107
- ZOE...

32:29.220 --> 32:41.599
WOULD YOU EVER CONSIDER
THAT I MAY ADOPT YOUR BABY?

32:41.710 --> 32:43.849
- UM...

32:43.960 --> 32:48.169
NO.

32:53.240 --> 32:55.583
- OUR PLAN IS TO TRY TO
HANG ONTO AS MUCH OF THESE

32:55.690 --> 32:58.579
FURNISHINGS AS POSSIBLE BECAUSE
IT'S SO AUTHENTIC AND THEN--OH,

32:58.700 --> 33:01.726
WE WHERE GONNA TRY TO MAKE THIS
FUNCTIONAL AGAIN.

33:01.840 --> 33:04.559
MAKE GRILLED CHEESES AND MALTS,
THAT KIND OF THING, YOU KNOW,

33:04.670 --> 33:07.491
SO THE MUSICIANS HAVE SOMETHING
TO SNACK ON IN BETWEEN.

33:07.600 --> 33:10.592
- GUYS, I AM GOTTA BE HONEST
WITH YOU.

33:10.710 --> 33:13.770
I'VE JUST GOT A GREAT OFFER
FROM ANOTHER DEVELOPER

33:13.880 --> 33:15.256
AND HE'S PRETTY SOLID.

33:15.370 --> 33:16.268
- REALLY?

33:16.370 --> 33:17.917
- WELL, THIS IS
A PRETTY UNIQUE SPACE.

33:18.030 --> 33:19.156
WHAT ARE THEY PLANNING ON DOING?

33:19.270 --> 33:20.885
- THEY GOT PRETTY MUCH RIPPED
EVERYTHING OUT

33:20.990 --> 33:24.266
AND PUT IN OFFICE SPACE.

33:24.380 --> 33:25.779
- ARE YOU KIDDING--
YOU'RE NOT KIDDING?

33:25.900 --> 33:27.299
THAT'S--THAT'S
A TERRIBLE IDEA.

33:27.410 --> 33:30.413
